 stroking his hand. 'A schoolfellow — a suspicious character,' explained Luzhin. 'But now dear Luzhin's all right,' whispered his wife and kissed his soft hand. 'Now everything's gone,' said Luzhin.

But this was not quite so. Something remained — a riddle, a splinter.

At nights he began to meditate over why this meeting had made him so uneasy. Of course there were all sorts of individual unpleasantnesses —

